      "date": "2011-10-20 21:24:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nIn this case, do you like to have this one, and discard the page in LU-334? Simpler is better, I like this one ;-)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "9c5a3b1f1e56e2bc12541e3a32028d05221dde0b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2011-10-20 23:20:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Jinshan,\n\nThe patches for LU-334 and LU-700 are independent.  I hope both can go through.  334 is an enhancement: we save monitors from having to map OSTs to mounts and visit one one stats file per OST.\n\n700 is a pure fix.  Some error cases encountered on TACC filesystems caused the BRW_{READ,WRITE}_BYTES counters to increase by incredible amounts; it would appear that clients were doing I/O at several times the local DRAM bandwidth.  Eat your heart out, Panasas and GPFS.\n\nThanks,\n\nJohn",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
